In his weekly address, President Trump talks about the importance of Women's History Month and pays tribute to influential women in American history. He then shifts the focus to healthcare, criticizing Obamacare and highlighting broken promises such as rising premiums, limited choice of plans, and lost insurance coverage. He emphasizes the urgent need to repeal and replace Obamacare, and mentions the House Republicans' plan that aims to empower states and consumers. The President also directs Secretary of Health and Human Services, Dr. Tom Price, to reduce regulations that drive up healthcare costs. He encourages Democrats to work together to improve the healthcare system and promises relief for American workers, families, and small businesses.